Fulton County Public Facilities will Close on Friday, September 27

Residents urged to prepare for potential power outages

Due to the anticipated impact of Hurricane Helene, Fulton County public facilities will remain closed to the public on Friday, September 27. This includes the Fulton County courthouse, all government centers, libraries, senior centers, and tax offices.

Fulton County staff will continue to work virtually to support residents. Many services are available online at www.fultoncountyga.gov. Residents may call the Fulton County Customer Service Line at 404-612-4000.

The Fulton County Animal Shelter will open for adoptions and limited intakes from 1 p.m. to 7 p.m. on Friday, September 27. Starting today at 4 p.m., field operations will continue for emergency calls and public safety support only until normal operations resume.

Residents may continue to tax services online at www.fultontaxes.com or by phone. Vehicle tags are also available through kiosks in Kroger stores.

The Fulton County Board of Health will also be open for virtual services only on Friday, September 27.

All Fulton County public safety services will continue. The Fulton County Sheriff‚Äôs Office will prioritize Jail operations to ensure the safety and security of detainees.

Public Works staff is monitoring water and sewer systems for any impact from flooding.

The Atlanta Fulton Emergency Management Agency is coordinating with all Fulton County public safety partners to prepare for this severe weather event.

Fulton County residents are encouraged to closely monitor weather conditions and prepare for possible power outages. Important preparedness steps include:

Charging mobile devices;
Making sure there is an adequate supply of bottled water, necessary medicines and nonperishable food; and
Ensuring they have a working flashlight with extra batteries.
Residents can sign up for Fulton Alerts Community Notifications (FALCON)  at

www.fultoncountyga.gov/falcon

For additional updates please log on to www.fultoncountyga.gov or follow Fulton County on social media @FultonInfo.

 

###

Fulton County will Close Public Facilities on September 26
Virtual Services will Continue

Fulton County public facing facilities will be closed on Thursday, September 26. This includes libraries, senior centers, and tax offices and government centers.

The Fulton County Courthouse will remain open for emergency matters. Jurors will not report on Thursday, September 26. In-person hearings will be rescheduled. Virtual proceedings will continue. Fulton County Probate Court will not hold weddings on Friday, September 26.

Residents may continue to access tax services online at www.fultoncountytaxes.org or by phone. Vehicle tags are also available through kiosks in Kroger stores.

Virtual services will continue for behavioral health and developmental disability clients.

The Fulton County Board of Health will close its facilities at 2 p.m. on Thursday, September 26 and will be open for virtual services only on Friday, September 27. Vital records will be available online only.

Fulton County Administrative departments will encourage employees to telework wherever possible while continuing virtual operations.

All public safety services will continue. The Fulton County Sheriff‚Äôs Office will prioritize Jail operations to ensure the safety and security of detainees.

Public Works staff will carefully monitor water sewer systems for impact from flooding.

The Atlanta Fulton Emergency Management Agency is coordinating with all Fulton County public safety partners to prepare for this severe weather event.  Fulton County residents are encouraged to closely monitor weather conditions and prepare for possible power outages.

For additional updates please log on to www.fultoncountyga.gov or follow Fulton County on social media @FultonInfo.

I'm sure Ryan Gosling is actually being considered for both roles as we've stated many times on the channel as most of you probably know Kevin fee meets with a lot of actors for a lot of different roles until they find the perfect role so I'm sure he's being considered for both perhaps one of these is the role that will get Ryan Golan in the MCU could be the Silver Surfer but it also could be Ghost Rider but I hope I hope it's not Dr Doom I love Ryan goling I don't think he would be the man for Dr Doom and according to another report from Jeff Snider the same one who reported these last two about the Silver Surfer in Galactus according to him Doom will reportedly appear in the Fantastic 4 but at the very end of the film this is in line with other reports that we've had in the past that he might just simply cameo in the Fantastic 4 for like 5 seconds or maybe they just simply mention his name Victor Von Doom but keep in mind and if you don't know this let me explain Victor Von Doom Dr Doom is basically one of the main characters in Avengers Secret Wars he is pretty much the main villain in both of the secret War Stories from the comics now obviously the MCU is doing it differently as they should obviously Kang is seemingly still going to be the main focus and a beyonder king variant seems to be the main villain of the entire multivers Saga and Secret Wars but they should definitely have do Doom in it especially after that Dr Doom Secret Wars Easter egg in the Deadpool in Wolverine trailer we talked about this in the breakdown but if you missed it at the very end of the Deadpool and Wolverine trailer Wolverine throws Deadpool through a wall Deadpool is laying on the ground and as Wolverine walks up and we see a shadow you can take a look on the left here and you can see a secret Wars comic but this specific comic they used is Secret Wars number five of eight with Dr Doom's face on the cover so what we are looking at here is a pretty big do Doom Easter egg and we know that Deadpool and Wolverine the movie is going to directly set up of Avengers Secret Wars it's even been reported that Deadpool and Wolverine are going to show a lot of universes kind of coming together collapsing a lot of the heroes will be taken from a lot of different universes and come into one place so perhaps if the Fantastic 4 film really does take place in Another Universe and they get brought into some area with all these other Heroes Dr Doom will join them yes Reed Richards is the smartest man alive but don't forget Dr Doom is incredibly smart as well he even attended college with Reed Richards he's insanely smart as well and he's also a sorcerer so I'm not sure how they're going to portray him in the Fantastic 4 film but if their universe is about to collapse I'm sure Dr Doom would know this and since he does know how smart Reed is and perhaps he has some sort of specific technology in the movie he might go to the Fantastic 4 to see what's up and possibly even try to save his life and that could take him over into whatever Universe they end up in and bring him into Secret Wars maybe not as a main villain but simply as one of the many different cameos that we are going to see in that movie so according to Jeff Snyder they are going to cast for Doom later on in production of the film which makes sense since he's only going to appear at the very end maybe even a post credit scene probably only get 10 seconds on screen if that it makes sense that they would get the rest of the cast locked in before obviously but this does make me even more excited for the Fantastic 4 we've had a lot of great things happen this week and this is just one more thing to make it awesome so let me know your thoughts about the cast and the casting choices in the comments down below would you like to see Ryan go play the Silver Surfer and would you like to see Javier bardam as galatis let me know your thoughts in the comments down below please don't forget to like the video and subscribe to stay up to date on the Fantastic 4 and the MCU we are also giving away a PS5 an Xbox series X and some Marvel Legends items all you have to do to enter the giveaway is subscribe to the channel and leave a comment down below we pick one winner at the end of each month you can find us on Instagram and Twitter and as always thank you all so much for watching wolf wolf

REMEMBERING A HERO: A local man who lost his life trying to save his housemates in a Midtown boarding house fire is being called a hero. 

The blaze broke out at a home along State Street NW on Dec. 13. Fire officials previously said six people were rescued from the burning home and three people died, including Stacy Redmond.

On Wednesday, friends and family gathered at the Kroger in Tucker, where Stacy worked to honor him. They said brought joy to both customers and co-workers.

Click the link in the bio for the full story.

NEWS RELEASE FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE: December 1, 2023 CONTACT: nancy.nydam@dph.ga.gov Salmonella Infections from Pre-cut Cantaloupe At least five Georgians sickened. ATLANTA ‚Äì The Georgia Department of Public Health (DPH) is urging Georgians to be cautious about eating pre-cut cantaloupe if they cannot verify its source. At least five people in Georgia have become infected with Salmonella likely due to eating the contaminated cantaloupe. Across the country, 117 people have also been sickened, nearly half requiring hospitalization. The Salmonella cases reported in Georgia range in age from 1-81. The cases are from different areas of the state, not concentrated in any one place. One individual was hospitalized but has since been released. The recalled cantaloupe is sold in Georgia at Sprouts Farmers Market, Trader Joes, and Kroger stores. The cantaloupe is sold as pre-cut chunks or in fruit mixes. Whole cantaloupes that are also part of the recall may have a sticker that says ‚ÄúMalichita‚Äù or ‚ÄúRudy‚Äù, with the number 4050 and ‚ÄúProduct of Mexico/produit du Mexique. ‚Äù More information about the recall can be found on the FDA website: https://www.fda.gov/food/outbreaks-foodborne-illness/outbreak-investigation-Salmonella-cantaloupes-november-2023. Most people infected with Salmonella experience diarrhea, fever, and stomach cramps and recover without treatment in 4-7 days. But the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC) is concerned about this outbreak because the illnesses associated with it are severe, including fevers higher than 102¬∞F, not being able to keep down liquids, and diarrhea that lasts more than three days without improving. Individuals who may have eaten the recalled cantaloupe should contact their healthcare provider if they have severe Salmonella symptoms. Do not eat pre-cut cantaloupe or whole cantaloupe if you don‚Äôt know whether it is Malichita or Rudy brand. If you have any of the recalled cantaloupe, throw it away or return it to the store where you purchased it. Rinsing pre-cut cantaloupe does not remove all germs if it is already contaminated with Salmonella. Rinsing whole cantaloupes can reduce the number of germs but it does not remove all germs. Germs on the surface of cantaloupes can then get onto the knife and inside the fruit when you cut the cantaloupe. Wash items and surfaces that may have touched the cantaloupe using hot soapy water or a dishwasher. For more information about the Salmonella outbreak, log on to https://www.cdc.gov/salmonella/sundsvall-11-23/index.html.

the grocery store instructed to do so after inspectors found rat waste and evidence the animals had been gnawing at the food yuck Atlanta news first Adam Murphy broke the story he joins us live tonight on South Atlanta Road near that grocery store Adam good evening good evening Sean the trailer loaded with that contaminated food is no longer here at the loading dock area at the Kroger on South Atlanta Road in Smyrna and staff spent the day cleaning up in this spot and making repairs to keep the rats out less than 24 hours after an Atlanta news first investigation uncovered a rat infestation inside the Kroger on South Atlanta Road in Smyrna we spotted workers cleaning the loading dock area and patching up drain holes to keep out the rodents customers were appalled I don't believe it I don't believe it right back here well hell no I don't believe it it's unfortunate but it's not surprising this this particular Kroger tends to be uh very LAX on Monday the Georgia Department of Agriculture shared photographs taken at the store which show rodent droppings and urine spots in the storage area the inspector also identified where rats had been gnawing on products and creating Burrows it does not surprise me that they have issues with rats because it just always seems like it's kind of a mess in there then Tuesday afternoon a state inspector took this video showing the contaminated products from the store being dumped out of a Kroger trailer and into the landfill as ordered by the Department of Agriculture I'm glad somebody spoke up but I've never noticed anything in the store her spokesperson said they are working with the state to eliminate the problem that said we did not see an inspection report posted within 15 feet of the entrance of the GoogleAudioText: Metro Atlanta Woman fights back after she was almost kidnapped at gunpoint outside a Kroger. This all happened in Marietta. This is right near the intersection of Delk and Powers Ferry Rd, which is considered a very busy area. 11 lives. Cody alcorn. You spoke with police and Cody, what do we know about this guy who tried to take this woman? Well, right now we can tell you Randy Harmon is a convicted felon. And listen to this. After police say he tried to kidnap the woman outside Kroger last week, he ditched her car and then was arrested the same night. In a different stolen vehicle. This isn't something that happens often, but on December 6th something did happen outside this Marietta Kroger 9 in the morning. On a Tuesday morning, on a busy intersection in the middle of all of this industry, Tamika Harris pulls into a parking spot. Little diseno that there's already a convicted felon who has backed into a spot and is looking for a victim. Once she walks inside, the convicted felon was seen on camera moving his car to be immediately next to her driver door to drive her door. Harris walks out, and as she's finishing unloading her groceries, officer Chuck Mcfillin me says the suspect attacked as she opens up her. Driver door to get in. She feels something jab into her side. It's a gun. He's forcing her over that center council. She has a choice. She fought him off. They wrestled over the weapon. He got into the car. He tried to accelerate in an attempt to kidnap her. She got the passenger door open and she fell out as he was speeding out of the parking lot. Harris's car was found a short time later, ditched in a nearby neighborhood, and not a single thing was missing. You have to ask yourself, if he wasn't after any of her belongings, then what did he want? Fortunately, Harris fought back. Thank God that she did, and thank God that she did things the way that she did, Officer Mcphilemy says while this crime is rare for their city, it's a good reminder it can happen to anyone at any time. But that's not a cause for fear. It's a request for just due diligence at situational awareness. As I mentioned, Randy Harmon was arrested the same night after Cobb County police got a hit on a flock camera alerting them of a stolen car. They tracked it down and arrested him. He's facing several felony charges now. As for Harris, she got a few bumps and bruises but was not seriously hurt.

GoogleAudioText: New tonight, Cobb County is hoping to decrease crime by using facial recognition software. Community members have been a little critical of this technology in the past, but what are they saying about it now? 11 lives? Karis Belger has their reaction. One member of the Cobb County Public Safety Coalition wants to make sure there are limits to the software, and after last night's community meeting, Sally Riddle says her concerns are alleviated. For now. Understanding is that the contract will begin shortly, but that they still will not allow use of the software until the policy is fully implemented and trained on. Sally Riddle says she was concerned when she first heard about Cobb County using Clearview AI. Software to solve crimes. We wanted to make sure that there was a good control over who would get to use the software within the Police Department, Riddle says. She was also concerned about the software being used to misidentify people of color, and that it would be used to invade the privacy of everyday people when it could be used. To make sure that it wasn't the sole determining factor in whether someone was pursued for a crime, the Cobb County Police Department has been using the software. For the last seven months there were pilot program Chief Stuart Van Hooser says police use images that are uploaded from public images that are already available and the tool is working. The first time we ever used it, it was a newspaper article that solved a four year old homicide, 3 1/2 year old homicide. Van Hoosier also understands the public safety concerns, but says there would be limits to who could use it and what it would be used for. And if we can't develop information that the person did it, then we're not going to rely on that tip, if that makes sense. For now, Sally says she's not worried, but she hopes the Police Department will keep its word. Riddle mentioned she's also concerned there isn't a statewide regulation of facial recognition software. She's hoping to push lawmakers to look more closely at how tools like Clearview AI are used. You know, I know they're using it in China all the time. A lot different, of course, being here in America. But a lot of folks are concerned about the Big Brother aspect of that, being able to spy on your family or you as well. That's the opportunity cost there, you know. What are you giving up to get the protection, to get the crime solved. So there's a lot of discussion that's gonna be, I think had going forward as more and more technologies like this becomes available for sure.

Last Sunday, the award-winning and all-natural sweetener brand SweetLeaf Stevia made their first-ever NASCAR Cup Series race appearance on JTG Daugherty Racing‚Äôs No. 47 Camaro ZL1 piloted by Ricky Stenhouse, Jr. in the Folds of Honor QuickTrip 500 at Atlanta Motor Speedway. SweetLeaf received great visibility on FOX as their driver led the field multiple times at the 1.54-mile re-paved oval. 

SweetLeaf not only co-sponsored the No. 47 Kroger Racing Camaro ZL1 this past weekend, but they also activated at a track for the second time this NASCAR Cup Series season. SweetLeaf Stevia‚Äôs display was set up in the Fan Zone near the Folds of Honor stage in a high traffic area and provided eager fans with samples of their products. In support of this initiative, Stenhouse Jr. made a special visit race day to sign specially made SweetLeaf autograph cards for fans. JTG Daugherty Racing will continue to work with SweetLeaf to heighten brand awareness during the 2022 NASCAR Cup Series season.
